&nbsp;MBOMBELA &#8211; Four local pupils recently won the Model United Nations (MUN) debating competition. The team comprised Maru Attwood and Thando Mathebula from Penryn College and Nthabele Khoza and Candice Morelo from Sitintile Secondary School in KaNyamazane. They competed in Cape Town from October 13 to 18 against 18 other teams from across the county. They had to represent a member state of the UN.